pull_request.title: feat: Include password in user creation and update return values
pull_request.body:
This pull request updates the user creation and update logic in the Postgres repository to ensure the `password` field is included in both the returned columns and the scanned struct after an insert or update operation. This change helps maintain consistency and ensures the full user model, including the password, is available after these operations.

**Repository query and model updates:**

* Added the `password` field to the list of returned columns in both the `Create` and `Update` user queries in `repository.go`, ensuring the password is populated in the resulting `User` model. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL53-R59) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL262-R269)
* Updated the `Scan` calls to include the `Password` field, so the `User` struct returned from these methods contains the password value. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL53-R59) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL262-R269)

Signed-off-by: Christophe Bedard <bedard.christophe@gmail.com>

Replace hero section background with enhanced particle system

Hero Section Changes:
- Removed purple gradient background effects (::before pseudo-element)
- Removed static radial gradients and pulse animation
- Simplified to clean dark background for better particle visibility

Enhanced Particle System:
- Increased particle frequency (100ms instead of 150ms)
- Larger particle sizes (3-11px instead of 2-8px)
- Higher opacity range (0.3-1.2 instead of 0.2-1.0)
- Longer particle lifespan (9000ms instead of 8000ms)
- More frequent colored particles (120ms instead of 200ms)

New Hero-Specific Particles:
- Added multi-directional particle spawning (bottom, left, right, top)
- Created 4 new animation types: floatUp, floatDown, floatRight, floatLeft
- Particles spawn from all screen edges with random trajectories
- Enhanced glow effects and rotation animations

Ambient Floating Particles:
- Added slow-moving ambient particles that float in place
- Created smooth scaling and position animations
- Longer duration ambient effects (18 seconds)
- Gentle pulsing opacity for atmospheric effect

Overall Effect:
- Hero section now has same dynamic particle system as rest of site
- More immersive and consistent visual experience
- Particles create living, breathing background environment

issue.title: feat: Include password in user creation and update return values
issue.body:
This pull request updates the user creation and update logic in the Postgres repository to ensure the `password` field is included in both the returned columns and the scanned struct after an insert or update operation. This change helps maintain consistency and ensures the full user model, including the password, is available after these operations.

**Repository query and model updates:**

* Added the `password` field to the list of returned columns in both the `Create` and `Update` user queries in `repository.go`, ensuring the password is populated in the resulting `User` model. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL53-R59) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL262-R269)
* Updated the `Scan` calls to include the `Password` field, so the `User` struct returned from these methods contains the password value. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL53-R59) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-68a3e6ef41ab86f6268ccb6d454351dd74ef6fb06662477dd88cf603ff9e92dbL262-R269)
